  "text": "Binding of Ag to FceRI on mast cells also triggers the activation of three families of mitogen-activated protein kinases (MAPKs) and nuclear factor (NF)-κB signaling pathways, which contribute to the inducible expression of inflammatory genes including cyclooxygenase (COX)-2 [CITATION_1] . In addition, activated MAPKs lead to the phosphorylation of cytosolic phospholipase A2 (cPLA2) and release of AA, a common precursor of eicosanoids [CITATION_2] .",
